race.comment: SHOOT THE DIVA (5) progressed nicely last time out when she made late ground to finish just 2 lengths from the winner in third over 1250m at Taree. Perfectly placed and is sure to prove tough to beat. GOLDEN COPPER (2) finished 2 lengths away in fourth last time out over 1100m at Port Macquarie when first up from a spell. Tackles a longer journey this time. Has the gate speed to take up a forward position. Sure to be in the finish. TESER (1) was prominent at the corner and progressed nicely last start to finish a close second over 1610m at Grafton after missing the placings at the previous appearance. Finds a more suitable contest and can find winning form. NOBLE MISSILE (4) is worth keeping safe fresh.
